SetProvider.returns:
 if the provider was registered successfully;
 if the authentication method has already been claimed
via application configuration and cannot be overridden.

SetProvider.example:
The following example demonstrates registering a provider for AOT applications:

  // At the top of Main(), before opening any connection:
  var provider = new ActiveDirectoryAuthenticationProvider(
      SqlAuthenticationProviderManager.ApplicationClientId);

  SqlAuthenticationProviderManager.SetProvider(
      SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryManagedIdentity, provider);
  SqlAuthenticationProviderManager.SetProvider(
      SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryDefault, provider);
